  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n\r\n/kind bug\r\n/area hw-accelerators\r\n/sig node\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nWhen re-writing the endpoint code I discovered that the [mutex logic](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/6b97376a539c84b9bb11de5d44daeadf9930049e/pkg/kubelet/cm/deviceplugin/endpoint.go#L96) is wrong and can lead to a data race while calling the `Device` function.\r\n\r\nThe current logic is a bit convoluted and would make more sense if the map was created in the for loop.\r\nHowever it seems like once the map is assigned to the structure, a device update while calling the `Device` function will lead to a data race,\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n/assign @jiayingz ",
